<span id="freeTextContainer11960375091398747717">Catton is an amazing writer, and this book on the period in which Grant took charge of the Army of the Potomac to defeat Lee was, at times, exciting. But for much of the time, it fell into that trap of many Civil War histories, becoming boring because it is just reciting this endless series of troop movements without really explaining what they meant or why they mattered. </span>

